The article discusses the strategy of the United States to counter the Islamic State of Iraq and the Levant (ISIL). The article states that ISIL poses a threat to Iraq, Syria, the Middle East, and the US homeland. The US has increased intelligence resources and sent personnel to assess the situation on the ground. They have conducted airstrikes to protect Americans and prevent humanitarian catastrophes. The US aims to degrade and destroy ISIL through a comprehensive and sustained counterterrorism strategy. The strategy includes supporting effective governance in Iraq, denying ISIL safe-haven, building partner capacity, enhancing intelligence collection, disrupting ISIL's finances, exposing ISIL's true nature, disrupting the flow of foreign fighters, protecting the homeland, and providing humanitarian support. The US will work with regional and international partners to achieve these goals.